Name: Animating Breaths
Description: Instead of using your Breath Weapon, you may instead spend 4 uses of it to summon an {@creature Animated Breath|ftd} related to your Chromatic ancestry. The Animated Breath is under your control and you can command it (no action required). It remains for 10 minutes.

Name: Ruthless Fire
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Graze|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. Additionally, before you attack a creature you may reduce your hit bonus by a value of your choosing. If you hit you deal twice this value in fire damage to the target.

Name: Master Moonstone Steps
Description: You get a teleport speed equal to your walking speed.

Name: Advanced Photosynthesis
Description: Your {@optfeature Photosynthesis|otherorenth} Trait functions whenever you are in bright light.

Name: Slowed Time Strikes
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Slow|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. However, instead of reducing their speed by 10 feet you may instead choose to give them the Dazed condition.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Vex
Description: After you use your {@optfeature Vex|ingensorenth} Orenth Trait you can choose to make an additional attack against them instead of gaining advantage. You may do so once per turn.

Name: Dragon Turtle Speed
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Slow|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. However, instead of reducing their speed by 10 feet you may instead choose to give them the Slowed condition.

Name: Human Variety
Description: The variety of humans leads to them being able to accomplish extraordinary feats. You gain a feat.

Name: School Mastered: Evocation
Prerequisite: Spell mastery with an Evocation school spell.
Description: You may downcast any Evocation spell that can be upcast of 2nd level or higher. When you do so reduce the number of damage dice in the same pattern as it gets increased for higher level spellslots.

Name: Mighty Recovery
Description: Choose a tier 1 Orenth trait that gives you a first level spellslot back. You may instead get a fith level spellslot back. The orenth type of this trait is the same as the tier 1 trait you choose.  You cannot choose the same tier 1 trait in this way twice.

Name: Exhaustive Magic
Description: Choose a first spell. You can cast this spell without expending a spellslot, but whenever you do you must make a Constitution saving throw (DC = 15). On a failure you gain one level of exhaustion.

Name: Swimming Through the Air
Description: You gain a flying speed equal to your swimming speed.

Name: Elevator Builder
Description: Over the course of a minute you may summon an elevator that safely takes you up to 1000 feet up into the air. The elevator can pass through up to 100 feet of stone or wood, but doesn't destroy anything. The elevator moves 50 feet up or down on initiative count 20, the direction is decided by you. Anyone can see you from outside the elevator. The elevator lasts for 24 hours. Uses: 1/Long rest

Name: The Stubbornest
Description: Whenever you fail a saving throw you may choose to succeed it instead. You may use this ability a number of times equal to the amount of Orenth traits you have with stubborn in them and regain all uses after a long rest.
